{
  "stem": "10818.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I mean, you know, we-- many times, we, we, we-- when we think of, of the Holocaust and those times, we think of those terrible trains and, and, and the extermination camps and how the people looked so terrible then.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And these were people who, before the war, had been just like you and me.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They were totally part of the populace.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "They were ordinary citizens or, or distinguished citizens in some cases.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And, you know, what Hitler essentially reduced them to were a non-people and, and, and just refugees and, and, and, and haunted, hunted people, as, as you know.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And before the war, they had been solid citizens and lived in rather, you know, in some cases, very pleasant circumstances.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They had been organized by the British, in order to get young people out, and sometimes, you know, real children into safety.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the British had this, what they thought was a wonderful idea that, you know, they could save these children, not by giving money here and there, the way we do it these days, but by offering them homes in which they could live or schools in which they could live and bringing them up there until it blew over.",
      "word_count": 60
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, it was bound to blow over sometime.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so many of us went on these kindertransports, which were essentially a collection of children who were brought on a train and then by ferry across the Channel and were delivered into sort of a central area, where they were then parceled out to people who would have them.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And in some cases, it was a disaster because they were forced to give up their identities, and, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and the people, you know, people are people everywhere.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They sometimes took advantage of them.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
